541
00:46:57,537 --> 00:46:59,293
So you're Vitus.

542
00:46:59,680 --> 00:47:01,720
Nice to meet you.

543
00:47:02,081 --> 00:47:03,990
Have a seat.

544
00:47:05,377 --> 00:47:07,711
What are you going to play for me?

545
00:47:09,377 --> 00:47:11,832
I'd like you to play something for me.

546
00:47:13,377 --> 00:47:14,489
Me?

547
00:47:15,489 --> 00:47:17,661
That's very flattering,

548
00:47:18,305 --> 00:47:21,120
but I'd rather listen to you

549
00:47:21,217 --> 00:47:24,151
playing Scarlatti's sonata in E minor.

550
00:47:25,665 --> 00:47:26,712
No.

551
00:47:27,137 --> 00:47:29,657
Okay, I'll play something for you,

552
00:47:29,761 --> 00:47:32,314
but it's your turn first.

553
00:47:40,129 --> 00:47:41,558
I don't feel like it.

554
00:47:42,945 --> 00:47:44,570
Do it for me.

555
00:47:44,833 --> 00:47:46,775
Why is it always for you?

556
00:47:50,081 --> 00:47:52,448
Don't worry, madam.

557
00:47:53,121 --> 00:47:55,260
It's more important for a pianist

558
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:58,524
to have good parents than good teachers.

559
00:47:59,393 --> 00:48:03,801
Vitus, you should play neither
for your mother nor me.

560
00:48:04,417 --> 00:48:07,035
Just take your time
until you feel like playing,

561
00:48:07,136 --> 00:48:10,170
playing the piano for the sake of the music.

562
00:48:13,153 --> 00:48:16,698
Cold rationality and a warm heart,

563
00:48:17,601 --> 00:48:21,310
that's what makes a great pianist.

564
00:48:23,425 --> 00:48:25,726
That's why I want to become a vet.

565
00:48:44,513 --> 00:48:46,902
Can I visit Grandpa for the weekend?

566
00:48:47,073 --> 00:48:48,414
No way!

567
00:48:54,624 --> 00:48:58,650
Do you have any idea how many youngsters
would like an opportunity like this?

568
00:48:59,713 --> 00:49:01,753
They come here from all over the world

569
00:49:01,856 --> 00:49:04,158
just for one single piano lesson, and you?

570
00:51:04,161 --> 00:51:05,503
Vitus?

571
00:51:26,816 --> 00:51:27,864
Has it come?

572
00:51:30,177 --> 00:51:31,354
Come on, sweetheart.

573
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:34,869
We're here!

574
00:51:43,457 --> 00:51:45,693
He was lucky.

575
00:51:46,913 --> 00:51:50,710
We couldn't find any injuries,

576
00:51:50,816 --> 00:51:52,987
not one bruise.

577
00:51:54,304 --> 00:51:57,600
Extraordinary, considering the heavy fall.

578
00:52:00,224 --> 00:52:02,428
There are miracles, though,

579
00:52:02,529 --> 00:52:04,765
especially with children.

580
00:52:05,505 --> 00:52:08,538
- The wings carried him for a bit.
- Yes.

581
00:52:09,281 --> 00:52:11,670
But he isn't an Icarus, luckily.

582
00:52:12,448 --> 00:52:13,790
He's still unconscious.

583
00:52:14,433 --> 00:52:18,556
At the moment, the initial diagnosis
is concussion of the brain.

584
00:52:18,849 --> 00:52:20,278
What do you mean, "At the moment"?

585
00:52:21,121 --> 00:52:25,693
There are injuries
which only show up after a few days.

586
00:52:25,792 --> 00:52:29,949
With brain injuries, you can never rule out

587
00:52:30,049 --> 00:52:32,089
long-term implications.

588
00:52:32,385 --> 00:52:34,010
I'll show you some pictures.

589
00:52:54,496 --> 00:52:55,991
You're taking a long time.

590
00:52:57,089 --> 00:52:58,398
Sorry.

591
00:52:59,777 --> 00:53:01,206
Well, I have plenty of time.

592
00:53:10,433 --> 00:53:11,448
Check!

593
00:53:24,448 --> 00:53:25,561
And what is this?

594
00:53:25,952 --> 00:53:27,992
Dad brought it.

595
00:53:29,569 --> 00:53:30,910
It's for my exams.

596
00:53:43,873 --> 00:53:45,247
Vitus, what are you doing?

597
00:53:45,664 --> 00:53:46,908
This isn't our car.

598
00:53:48,481 --> 00:53:50,390
Come on.

599
00:54:20,513 --> 00:54:21,854
<i>The following, Mrs. von Holzen.</i>

600
00:54:22,048 --> 00:54:25,463
We have tested
his speaking and reading skills,

601
00:54:26,017 --> 00:54:28,831
his memory and his sense of perception.

602
00:54:29,024 --> 00:54:32,253
We got normal levels.

603
00:54:32,929 --> 00:54:34,816
What does "normal levels" mean?

604
00:54:35,328 --> 00:54:36,408
Please, take a seat.

605
00:54:36,960 --> 00:54:38,684
Normal according to his age group.

606
00:54:39,105 --> 00:54:42,138
He's even slightly above average,

607
00:54:42,241 --> 00:54:44,150
especially in his logical thinking.

608
00:54:45,313 --> 00:54:46,971
- And the IQ test?
- Yes?

609
00:54:47,072 --> 00:54:49,974
- Did you do...
- Yes, but, at the moment,

610
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:52,414
the test is irrelevant,

611
00:54:52,512 --> 00:54:55,643
but if you really want to know,
it's around 120.

612
00:54:57,568 --> 00:54:58,975
120?

613
00:54:59,873 --> 00:55:02,590
It used to be 180. How is that possible?

614
00:55:04,192 --> 00:55:05,240
I know.

615
00:55:07,008 --> 00:55:08,055
It's difficult to say.

616
00:55:09,984 --> 00:55:13,759
Even for specialists like us,
the brain remains a mystery.

617
00:55:15,520 --> 00:55:20,060
There's no real explanation
for extraordinary abilities.

618
00:55:24,768 --> 00:55:27,070
If I can give you some advice,

619
00:55:27,168 --> 00:55:31,838
give yourself and Vitus some time.
Time, time, time.

620
00:55:31,936 --> 00:55:34,391
He'll make some progress.

621
00:55:36,736 --> 00:55:38,427
You just want to cheer me up.

622
00:55:39,585 --> 00:55:40,599
Many thanks.

623
00:55:41,345 --> 00:55:43,548
I cannot understand your disappointment.

624
00:55:43,648 --> 00:55:46,463
After all, you have a healthy
and normal child.

625
00:55:46,561 --> 00:55:49,594
I have to give
worse news to a lot of parents.

626
00:55:55,616 --> 00:55:57,274
Listen, everybody!

627
00:55:57,825 --> 00:55:59,134
Silence, please!

628
00:55:59,552 --> 00:56:01,407
Daniel, please!

629
00:56:02,080 --> 00:56:05,822
This is your new schoolmate, Vitus.

630
00:56:05,920 --> 00:56:09,662
He has changed schools,
and he's with us from now on.

631
00:56:09,760 --> 00:56:13,175
Vitus, you can sit next to Jens.

632
00:56:20,320 --> 00:56:22,043
Hi, Vitus, what's up?

633
00:56:22,144 --> 00:56:23,224
Hi, Jens.

634
00:56:25,248 --> 00:56:28,248
Like this. Loosen up.

635
00:56:28,352 --> 00:56:29,977
Now make a fist.

636
00:56:30,752 --> 00:56:32,476
Yes, that's right. And again.

637
00:56:51,872 --> 00:56:55,614
Play the run, and take your time.

638
00:57:10,816 --> 00:57:13,500
"Es!" Doesn't it hurt your ears?

639
00:57:13,600 --> 00:57:16,502
At least your fingers
should be able to remember.

640
00:57:17,409 --> 00:57:18,456
Sorry.

641
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:21,943
Music comes from the heart,
from your fingers, from your soul!

642
00:57:23,265 --> 00:57:25,403
All you hurt was your head.

643
00:57:29,025 --> 00:57:30,912
Sorry, Mom.

644
00:58:06,113 --> 00:58:07,967
Don't you feel lonely sometimes?

645
00:58:08,736 --> 00:58:09,914
Yes, I do.

646
00:58:11,104 --> 00:58:13,406
Loneliness is the worst,

647
00:58:15,009 --> 00:58:19,165
but I'm doing something about it.

648
00:58:20,192 --> 00:58:22,843
- I write love letters.
- To whom?

649
00:58:25,856 --> 00:58:29,369
Up to now, I've only written to Annemarie,
but now I'm getting more generous.

650
00:58:29,472 --> 00:58:31,447
I'm also writing to the beautiful woman

651
00:58:32,480 --> 00:58:34,936
who sat opposite me in the train

652
00:58:35,040 --> 00:58:36,829
and to the glistening lake,

653
00:58:38,432 --> 00:58:40,799
to the lovely figure skater on TV

654
00:58:41,856 --> 00:58:45,020
and to the cool shade under the pear tree.

655
00:58:45,216 --> 00:58:47,191
- And then?
- And then?

656
00:59:08,161 --> 00:59:10,015
They fly beautifully.

657
00:59:11,136 --> 00:59:12,663
Fabulous.

